Reference-contexts: The throughput varies from user to user depending on the resolution and refresh rate of each users display. The latency bound is more relaxed (lip-sync delays of up to 100ms are tolerable for videoconferencing <ref> [18] </ref>) and often common to all users. Although different users and sources generally have different image formats and resolutions, we can perform rate conversion for each source (frame dropping/repeating and up/down sampling) such that all inputs have identical atom and frame rates. <p> Source contention or user contention appears unavoidable because, as we show later, it is impossible to perform multi-source, multi-user compositing without some form of source or user buffering. 3.0 Memory Efficient Strategies One multi-user compositing scheme has been suggested by Lukacs <ref> [18] </ref>. In this approach, none of the user streams are buffered, so user contention does not exist.
